                    <desc_content>
                        <paragraph>Authenticate with the Keystone service.</paragraph>
                        <paragraph>There are a few scenarios to consider here:</paragraph>
                        <enumerated_list enumtype="arabic" prefix="" suffix=".">
                            <list_item>
                                <paragraph>Which version of Keystone are we using? v1 which uses headers to
                                    pass the credentials, or v2 which uses a JSON encoded request body?</paragraph>
                            </list_item>
                            <list_item>
                                <paragraph>Keystone may respond back with a redirection using a 305 status
                                    code.</paragraph>
                            </list_item>
                            <list_item>
                                <paragraph>We may attempt a v1 auth when v2 is what’s called for. In this
                                    case, we rewrite the url to contain /v2.0/ and retry using the v2
                                    protocol.</paragraph>
                            </list_item>
                        </enumerated_list>
                    </desc_content>
                </desc>
